**Component:** `Strategy Candidate Generator`
   - *Description*: Identifies and clusters price levels to detect high-probability trade setups. It maps historical price action against ingested levels to generate "candidates"—discrete entry opportunities that serve as the input for the simulation engine.
   - *Source Group Names*: Trade Candidate Generator
   - *Key Entities*: `QName:`lib.backtest-data.long-candidate-generator.clusterLevels` FileRef: `lib/backtest-data/long-candidate-generator.js``
**Component:** `ATM Execution Simulator`
   - *Description*: The core simulation engine that applies Automated Trade Management (ATM) logic to trade candidates. It calculates real-time PnL, manages stop-loss/take-profit adjustments based on bar-by-bar price movement, and generates detailed performance reports in Markdown format.
   - *Source Group Names*: ATM Strategy Simulator
   - *Key Entities*: `QName:`lib.backtest-data.atm-simulator.simulateTrade` FileRef: `lib/backtest-data/atm-simulator.js``
**Component:** `Performance Analytics & Audit`
   - *Description*: Provides the statistical feedback loop by analyzing simulation outcomes. It audits "coverage" (how many signals were captured) and "alignment" (how signals performed relative to heatmap confluences), producing win-rate metrics that drive system optimization.
